vehicles.description: Several parked cars to the right of the ego car, aligned along the curb, with colors ranging from dark to light.
vehicles.explanation: The parked cars represent static obstacles which the ego car should keep a safe distance from to avoid any potential door openings or pedestrians emerging from in between the vehicles.

vehicles.description: A black car on the right side of the road, positioned parallel to the ego car, appears to be stationary with no visible brake lights or turn signals.
vehicles.explanation: This vehicle is parked, therefore it does not pose an immediate threat, but the ego car should be cautious in case the vehicle starts moving or a door opens suddenly.

traffic lights.description: There are street lights illuminating the road, but no visible traffic lights in the image to indicate the status of traffic control signals.
traffic lights.explanation: Without traffic lights in view, the ego car should proceed based on the road rules that apply to the area, while remaining prepared to stop or yield if upcoming traffic lights are encountered.

other objects.description: Trash bins and garbage bags on the curb to the right side of the driving lane, adjacent to the parked cars.
other objects.explanation: These objects should be noted for the potential of unexpected movement, such as being toppled over or animals emerging, which could affect the driving path of the ego car.

suggestions: The ego car should maintain a moderate speed, accounting for reduced visibility due to nighttime conditions. It ought to keep a safe distance from the parked cars to the right to avoid any unexpected obstructions and remain alert for any emergent road signs or changes in road conditions. Additionally, the presence of trash bins suggests the ego car should be cautious and ready to react if any small animals emerge onto the road.
